---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="death"
  description="death index / dance of death, grief, afterlife, memento mori, death and rebirth"
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-kicker">death / archive wing / index</div>
    <h1>death</h1>
    <p>
      endings, mortality, grief, remembrance, and the strange clarity that comes
      when life is seen against its limit. death is not only an event, but a
      condition that shapes meaning.
    </p>
    <p class="muted">
      this wing explores death symbolically, psychologically, and existentially—
      not as something separate from life, but as something that gives life its
      edge, seriousness, and depth.
    </p>
  </section>

  <div class="box">
    <div class="box-title">entry sequence</div>
    <div class="box-body">
      <div class="grid-links">
        <a href="/death/dance-of-death">
          <span class="link-title">dance of death</span>
          <span class="link-desc">mortality, equality, irony, and inevitability.</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/death/impermanence">
          <span class="link-title">impermanence</span>
          <span class="link-desc">change, passing, instability, and the nature of all things.</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/death/afterlife">
          <span class="link-title">afterlife</span>
          <span class="link-desc">continuation, myth, vision, and the unknown.</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/death/memento-mori">
          <span class="link-title">memento mori</span>
          <span class="link-desc">remembering death as a way of living clearly.</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/death/rebirth">
          <span class="link-title">death + rebirth</span>
          <span class="link-desc">cycles of ending, renewal, and return.</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="box">
    <div class="box-title">how to read</div>
    <div class="box-body">
      <p>
        death appears in more than one form. physical death is only one layer.
        loss, disappearance, endings, severance, and irreversible change all
        belong to the same field.
      </p>
      <p>
        read this section slowly. death tends to simplify what is false and make
        what matters harder to ignore.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="box">
    <div class="box-title">death map</div>
    <div class="box-body">
      <p><a href="/death/dance-of-death" class="link-red">dance of death</a> — inevitability, irony, equality</p>
      <p><a href="/death/impermanence" class="link-blue">impermanence</a> — change, passing, instability</p>
      <p><a href="/death/afterlife" class="link-green">afterlife</a> — continuation, myth, unknown</p>
      <p><a href="/death/memento-mori">memento mori</a> — mortality, clarity, presence</p>
      <p><a href="/death/rebirth">death + rebirth</a> — renewal, cycle, transformation</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="box">
    <div class="box-title">note</div>
    <div class="box-body">
      <p class="muted">
        this wing is arranged as a circular path: dance of death → impermanence → afterlife
        → memento mori → death + rebirth → back to dance of death.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
